fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.config

Interface IConfigStore

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IConfigUnit, Iterable<String>

    public interface IConfigStore
extends IConfigUnit
    Manages read/write configuration properties and provides support for persistent storage.

    Configuration stores can be used directly in for-each constructs, to iterate over property names.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent read/write access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IConfigService.createConfigStore(IConfigStoreEventListener, IConfigServiceEventListener), IConfigService.createAuxiliaryConfigStore(String, IConfigStoreEventListener, IConfigServiceEventListener), IConfigResource

    throws ConfigException

        Throws:

        Since:

        See Also:

      • isAutoStoreEnabled

        boolean isAutoStoreEnabled()
        Determines if auto-store is enabled.

        When auto-store is enabled, any call to a set or remove method automatically saves the entire configuration. When auto-store is disabled, changes are stored in memory (and available via the various get methods) but are only saved to the persistent backing storage after a successful store.

        Returns:
        true if auto-store is enabled, or false (the default) if store() must be called to store any changes.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        setAutoStoreEnabled(boolean), store()

      • setAutoStoreEnabled

        void setAutoStoreEnabled(boolean enabled)
                  throws ConfigException
        Enables or disables auto-store.

        If there is any unsaved data (if auto-store is disabled prior to calling this method and if there have been changes to properties), then this method will automatically attempt to store these changes before enabling auto-store. If changes cannot be saved, an exception is thrown, and auto-store remains disabled.

        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enable auto-store, or false to disable this feature.
        Throws:
        ConfigException - if auto-store cannot be enabled due to a failure to store any pending property changes.
        Since:
        1.0
